4. **Evaluation Metrics:**
   - **R-D Performance:** Evaluate the rate-distortion performance of the proposed approach to ensure efficient data transmission.
   - **Adaptability to SNR Conditions:** Measure how well the model adapts to varying SNR conditions, ensuring robust performance across different network scenarios.
   - **Computational Efficiency:** Assess the computational efficiency of the proposed approach, ensuring that it can be implemented in real-time systems.
   - **Comparison with Baselines:** Compare the results with existing methods to demonstrate the superiority of the proposed approach.

### Detailed Methodology

**Modeling Network Conditions with GNNs:**
- **Architecture:** Use Position-aware GNNs (P-GNNs) and Identity-aware GNNs (ID-GNNs) to model the network topology and link qualities dynamically.
- **Message Passing:** Implement message-passing mechanisms to propagate information about link qualities and SNR conditions across the network.

