SNR values.\n\n4. **Expected Outcomes:**\n   - Clearly define the expected improvements in R-D performance and adaptability.\n   - Discuss potential practical applications and implications for future research.\n\n### Refined Research Proposal\n\n**High-level summarized insight of a research field Machine Learning:**\nMachine learning, particularly graph neural networks (GNNs), can significantly enhance the efficiency and robustness of data transmission in mobile multi-hop networks by addressing the challenges posed by varying link qualities and SNR conditions.\n\n**Here are the five core questions:**\n\n**[Question 1] - What is the problem?**\nHow can we leverage graph neural networks (GNNs) to develop a robust and adaptive deep joint source-channel coding (DeepJSCC) framework that overcomes the limitations of existing methods and efficiently handles varying link qualities and SNR conditions in mobile multi-hop networks?\n\n**[Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?**\nSolving this problem is crucial for advancing the field of data transmission in mobile networks, enabling more efficient and reliable communication. This research will contribute to the development of next-generation communication systems that can adapt to dynamic network conditions, leading to improved performance and user experience. By using GNNs, we can model complex network topologies and adapt coding strategies in real-time, which is a significant step forward in the field.\n\n**[Question 3] - Why is it hard?**\nThe problem is challenging due to the complexity of modeling varying link qualities and SNR conditions, the need for sophisticated initialization methods, and the difficulty of dynamically adjusting scaling factors and coding strategies. Naive approaches may fail to provide optimal solutions, and existing methods often struggle with sub-optimal performance and adaptability. Integrating GNNs to dynamically model and adapt to network conditions adds another layer of complexity.\